Package com.persistentsystems.socketclient.listeners

Interface WrAsyncSocketListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TestAsyncClient, TestClient3Async, TestClient3AsyncNetwork, TestClientIperf
    public interface WrAsyncSocketListener
    This interface MUST be implemented by any class using an WrAsyncSocket. Set the listener by WrAsyncSocket.setSocketListener(WrAsyncSocketListener). Alternatively, an anonymous implementation can be used in WrAsyncSocket.setSocketListener(WrAsyncSocketListener).

      • onOpen

        void onOpen​(WrAsyncSocket xSocket)
     throws WebSocketTimeout
        Called when the websocket has opened. This is how you'll know the websocket has opened properly. And where you'll be able to issue your initial get/set/validates without having to worry about a timer or sleep of some sort.
        Parameters:
        xSocket - websocket that has opened
        Throws:
        WebSocketTimeout - thrown if the conneciton times out.
